250 g Ground Beef
6 unit(s) Flour Tortillas
85 g Tortilla Chips
1 unit(s) Sour Cream
113 g Corn Kernels
1 tbsp Mexican Seasoning
1 cup Cheddar Cheese, shredded
3 tbsp Guacamole
1 tbsp Tex-Mex Paste
1.5 tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat.
When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then beef, Tex-Mex paste, Mexican Seasoning and corn.
Cook, breaking up beef into smaller pieces, until no pink remains, 4-5 min.**
Season with salt and pepper.

On a clean surface, arrange tortillas.
Add beef mixture on one side of each tortilla. Top with tortilla chips (about 3-4 chips per tortilla), then sprinkle cheese over top.
Fold each tortilla over onto itself and firmly press to close.
Arrange quesadillas on a foil-lined baking sheet.

Brush quesadillas with 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil.
Broil in the middle of the oven, flipping halfway through cooking, until golden-brown and cheese has melted, 2-3 min per side.

Stir together sour cream and guacamole in a small bowl.
Divide beef crunch quesadillas between plates.
Serve remaining tortilla chips and creamy guacamole on the side for dipping.

If you've opted to get beef, cook it in the same way the recipe instructs you to cook the turkey.**